> Pesto: you've had it on pasta or maybe as a dip. Let us introduce you to yet another
> way to use this Italian favorite. Here, we're spreading it onto oven-roasted
> chicken breasts, using it as a glue to hold down a layer of panko breadcrumbs.
> That way, you get herby aromatics, meaty juices, and crispy golden goodness in
> every bite. Sounds like a crowd-pleaser to us.

Wash and dry all produce. Adjust rack to upper position and preheat oven to 450
degrees. Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{24%ounce} into ½-inch cubes.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{} and a
pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast in oven until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes},
tossing halfway through.

Stir together @panko breadcrumbs{1%cup}, @mozzarella cheese{1%cup}, a large
drizzle of @olive oil{}, and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{} in a #small bowl{}.

Place @chicken breasts{24%ounce} on another, lightly oiled baking sheet. Brush
1 TBSP @pesto{4%ounce} onto top of one piece. Repeat with remaining chicken (you
will have a little pesto left over). Press crust mixture into pesto to adhere.
Roast in oven until chicken is no longer pink in center, about ~{20%minutes}.

Halve @lemon{1%unit}. In a #large bowl{}, toss together @mixed greens{4%ounce},
a squeeze or two of lemon, and @olive oil{4%tsp}. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

Divide potatoes and chicken between plates. Serve with salad on the side.